$$
where we have used $1 \mathrm{~J}=1 \mathrm{~kg} \mathrm{~m}^2 \mathrm{~s}^{-2}$.

At a temperature $T$, the ratio of the spectral density of states at a wavelength $\lambda_1$ to that at $\lambda_2$ is given by
