To relate $k$ to $\nu_e$, we need the reduced mass $\mu=m_1 m_2 /\left(m_1+m_2\right)$. One mole of ${ }^{12} \mathrm{C}$ has a mass of $12 \mathrm{~g}$ and contains Avogadro's number of atoms. Hence the mass of one atom of ${ }^{12} \mathrm{C}$ is $(12 \mathrm{~g}) /\left(6.02214 \times 10^{23}\right)$. The reduced mass and force constant are
$$
